Sangrita recipe via @liquor 

Ingredients:
15 ounces tomato juice
6 ounces grapefruit juice, freshly squeezed
6 ounces orange juice, freshly squeezed
2 ounces lime juice, freshly squeezed
2 ounces Tabasco
2 teaspoons black pepper, freshly ground
1 teaspoon salt
1 jalapeño pepper, halved (with seeds)

Steps:

1. Add the tomato juice, grapefruit juice, orange juice, lime juice, Tabasco, black pepper, salt and jalapeño pepper into a pitcher and stir until the salt dissolves.

2. Let stand for 15 to 30 minutes, then remove and discard the jalapeño. (The longer the jalapeño infuses, the spicier the Sangrita will be.)

Trust me, he will marry you after this meal! 🤣🥰

* Mix together the steak and Italian seasonings, then rub that seasoning all over the roast. Spray your slow cooker with evoo. Add the spice rubbed roast and the broth. I like to wait to add potatoes, carrots, onions, and celery to the slow cooker halfway through the cooking time. Put the lid on and cook on low for 8 hours or on high for 6. 
* Make the gravy when the beef pot roast is done in the slow cooker. Drain the liquid from the bottom of the slow cooker into a sauce pan. Add to that the salt, pepper, garlic powder, and onion powder and let it come to a boil. 
* Next, in a small dish, whisk together the cornstarch and cold water. Add that to the saucepan and turn the heat down to medium-low. Let it cook and stir occasionally until the sauce thickens. That will only take about 3-5 minutes. 
* Time to eat! Pour the gravy back into the slow cooker and enjoy over mashed potatoes or rice. 

Ingredients
▢ 3 pounds chuck or rump roast 
▢ 2 tablespoons steak seasoning
▢ 1 tablespoon Italian seasoning
▢ 2 cups beef broth
▢ 1 pound baby carrots
▢ 2 pounds potatoes - cut into quarters
▢ 1 large white or yellow onion - cut into chunks
▢ 1 stalk celery - chopped
▢ 2 teaspoons salt - (or more to taste)
▢ 1 teaspoon black pepper - (or to taste)
▢ 2 teaspoons garlic powder
▢ 1 teaspoon onion powder
▢ 3 tablespoons cold water
▢ 3 tablespoons corn starch

Itzcali’s favorite smoothie is so simple to make!
She doesn’t love meat so I try and sneak in as much protein as possible. 

The base always stays the same: 
Greek Yogurt
Monat Vegan Protein Powder 
Frozen fruit

For the liquid I use either almond milk, water or orange juice. She LOVES her protein smoothie. I think the key was finding a clean, vegan protein that actually tastes delicious. 

What makes this protein different?
It contains proteins from 17 different superfoods!
Pea Protein Isolate
Pea protein is sourced from split yellow or green peas, or Pisum sativum. The peas are dried and ground into a fine powder. After the starch and fiber is removed, the remaining powder is considered an isolate, or pure protein.

Pumpkin Seed Protein
Derived directly from the nutrient-rich seeds of pumpkins, specifically Curcurbita pepo, the seeds are gently milled into a powder to create a versatile and highly digestible source of vegetable protein.

Sunflower Seed Protein
Sunflower seeds are technically the fruit of the sunflower plant Helianthus annuus and have a mild flavor and tender texture.

Chia Seed Protein
Chia seeds are the tiny black seeds of the chia plant Salvia hispanica. Chia seed protein is the isolated protein that remains after the fat and fiber components of the seed are removed.

Watermelon Seed Protein
Watermelon seeds have more nutritional value per weight than the fruit. The seeds are sprouted then roasted to make them digestible. Watermelon seed protein has gained popularity among vegans for its versatility and neutral flavor profile.

Rice Protein
Rice protein is created from the seed of the Oryza sativa plant. While rice has been known as a carbohydrate, rice protein isolate removes nearly all of the starch, leaving a pure and neutral-tasting protein.

Mushroom Blend
Chaga, cordyceps, lion’s mane, maitake, and turkey tail extracts have been used around the world for centuries in traditional remedies.
